<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>PyVideo.org</title><link>https://pyvideo.org/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://pyvideo.org/feeds/speaker_thomas-j-fan.rss.xml" rel="self"></atom:link><lastBuildDate>Tue, 05 Nov 2019 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Deep Dive into scikit-learn's HistGradientBoosting Classifier and Regressor</title><link>https://pyvideo.org/pydata-new-york-city-2019/deep-dive-into-scikit-learns-histgradientboosting-classifier-and-regressor.html</link><description>&lt;h3&gt;Description&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gradient boosting decision trees (GBDT) is a powerful machine-learning technique known for its high predictive power with heterogeneous data. In this talk, we will explore scikit-learn's implementation of histogram-based GBDT called HistGradientBoostingClassifier/Regressor and how it compares to other GBDT libraries such as XGBoost, CatBoost, and LightGBM.&lt;/p&gt;
